A year ago, I couldn't get out of my bed without help. Doctors gave me a list of limitations, and I wasn't having it. I cried, screamed, and prayed. That lidt would not ne my life. I didn't know how I was going to do it but I got out of that bed. I was going to do what they said I couldn't. 
What started as a suggestion, turned into me pushing my trainer across the room. He has no idea what milestones I accomplished today. Everything we did today I was told I would never do again. "Can't" don't live here. Anything is possible.

You have two choices when you see a fire: you can put it out, or you can pour on gasoline. 
If you don't want a fire, don't create space where fire will thrive. Don't bring in your anger. Don't come in here with your indignation. Those things are not bad on their own, but they're fuel. Don't just come in here and dump it. 
Come in with grace, beauty with an intention to build something. 
This space is ours. We choose the story. We are the narrative. And you have ownership of a piece of that. You have the responsibility for your piece of that. You have the responsibility for the energy you bring into this space. So please, choose with Grace, with Intention, and with Beauty.
